# SplitBae — Architecture & Discipline

## Product
High-performance platform-adaptive bill splitting (“Splid + Splitty”): **lean APK/IPA**, **offline-first**, **sync-ready**, no heavy on-device AI.

## Stack & visual language (strict)
- **Flutter** | **State: `flutter_riverpod`** for app/feature state — no `provider`, `ChangeNotifierProvider`, or ad-hoc global state. **`setState`** only for ephemeral local UI (focus, single-tick animation), not business/cross-screen.
- **Motion: `flutter_animate`** | **Icons: `phosphor_flutter`** (new work; skip if existing assets suffice). Both in `pubspec.yaml`.
- **No generic M2 or unthemed M3 chrome** (e.g. default `AppBar` + flat `Card` with no system). **Hybrid: M3 Expressive + Liquid Glass**, repo + attached **@Docs**.
  - **M3E:** `mergeMaterialExpressive`, `lib/core/theme/splitbae_material_expressive.dart`, `SplitBaeV0Layout` (`splitbae_v0_ui_contract.dart`). Docs: **@tofu_expressive**, **@m3e_design**, **@app_bar_m3e**, **@m3e_collection** — verify APIs; don’t invent.
  - **Liquid Glass:** **Liquid Glass Easy** and/or `SplitBaeShellTokens`, `SplitBaeFrostedPanel`, `lib/core/shell/adaptive_home_screen.dart`. **Blur only shell chrome** (bars, FAB area, rail) — never full scroll content.
  - **iOS:** **Cupertino Native Better** or repo Cupertino+shell when it helps fidelity; else **adaptive** (`showAdaptiveDialog`, `SwitchListTile.adaptive`, …).
- **Agents:** Use **@Docs** + `lib/core/theme/` — no invented widgets/APIs. Small composable (mostly stateless) widgets; **no 500+ line files**. User pastes **terminal output** → fix **root cause** without breaking layouts/tests. **v0/React/Tailwind** from `vercel/…`: drop React logic; port **visual hierarchy** only — Tailwind spacing → **M3E / `SplitBaeV0Layout`**; shadcn-like → **Liquid Glass / shell**.

## UI (all platforms)
- **Native-first:** M3 + Cupertino, **adaptive** primitives; custom UI only for clear product value (e.g. v0 shell tokens), not decoration.
- **Perf:** Hot path **Rust** + tight Dart; avoid redundant rebuilds, huge `BackdropFilter`, pointless custom painters — **profile** before micro-opts.
- **DRY:** `ThemeExtension`, shared tokens; repeat patterns → **once** in `core/` or `widgets/shell/`.
- **Parity:** Same MVP on phone/foldable/tablet/desktop, **iOS/Android/macOS** — layout adapts; no “lite” OS unless impossible (**issue** with why).
- **Current-gen via Flutter stable:** **M3 Expressive** on Android (`mergeMaterialExpressive`, dynamic color); **Liquid Glass–style shell** on Apple (`SplitBaeShellTokens`, `SplitBaeFrostedPanel`). Prefer new **Flutter/Material/Cupertino** expressive APIs when they land — refactor shell tokens to wrap them.
- **One IA, dual chrome:** Shared structure (Bills · Balances, search + profile, FAB roles/order, wide = rail + content, scan → draft). **Implementation** OS-native (M3 vs Cupertino, glass vs elevation) — don’t clone one OS on the other.

## Git (trunk)
Single remote; **small vertical commits**; **`main`/`trunk` releasable** (short branches or direct); **GitHub Issues** — prefer **one issue per small feature**.

## v0 → MVP
- **`vercel/SplitBae_v76_Vercel.v0/`**: IA, interactions, flows — **not** the shipping stack. Same **behavior** in **SQLite + Rust + Dart**, native UI.
- Workflows to implement: **transaction history**, **categories**, **per-transaction payments**, **settlements** (semantics + persistence) — not v0 React.
- **Insights** (trends, streaks): **not MVP**; ship later without blocking core.
- **l10n:** English-first `lib/l10n/app_en.arb` + identifiers; other locales on top.
- **Forward-compat:** Versioned migrations, nullable FKs (trips/sync IDs), single DB/repo layer, **additive** backups — avoid ad-hoc SQL/columns that block **sync / CRDT / multi-ledger**.

## Engineering
- **Modular:** `core/` has **no feature imports**; many small files, no god widgets.
- **Lean:** No bundled LLM for OCR. Rust: math/settlement/merge; Flutter: UI/I/O; SQLite: local state; **CRDT** only when sync — after MVP storage is solid.
- **Quality:** Product-grade naming; explicit types at **FRB**, storage, exports; no filler comments.
- **Rust owns math:** No tax/tip/split/minor-unit logic in `lib/` (no `total * 0.1` etc.). All in `rust/src/api/` (e.g. `simple.rs`), **flutter_rust_bridge**. Dart: **display** (`intl`/`NumberFormat`), **persist**; amounts via FRB (`amount_to_minor_units` / `minor_units_to_amount`).
- **Typography:** No global `ThemeData.fontFamily` forcing one face — M3/Cupertino defaults (**SF** / **Roboto+OEM**). No gratuitous `letterSpacing` on headlines.
- **Platform:** `dynamic_color` (Android 12+), **`configureSplitBaePlatform()`**, **haptics** on primary mobile nav, **shortcuts** desktop (`lib/core/platform/`). **`hostPlatformIsApple()`**: narrow → **`CupertinoPageScaffold`**; wide → Material **`Scaffold` + rail**. **Never** override engine **`MediaQuery`** (text scaler, bold, reduce-motion) — use **`splitBaeMaterialTheme`**, **`splitBaeAppBuilder`**, theme-relative **`TextStyle`**.

## Platform presentation (detail)
- v0 = **IA + flows**, not Tailwind/React fidelity. Ship **M3/Cupertino** + adaptive on **all** form factors; **macOS** same feature set.
- **Cross-OS:** Aligned labels, icon semantics, **task order**; **l10n**; prefer **shared** interaction patterns (e.g. adaptive dialog vs one-OS-only sheet).
- **v0 parity:** Tabs, FAB, scan, draft split, sheets. Structure: **`SplitBaeV0Layout`**. Chrome: **`SplitBaeShellTokens`** — Android **`splitbae_material_expressive.dart`**; Apple **LG** via `SplitBaeFrostedPanel`, `SplitBaeShellChromeIconButton`, `SplitBaeAdaptiveBottomNav`, wide rail in **`adaptive_home_screen.dart`**. **Chrome-only blur** (repeat: not full content).
- **Color:** Android — `ColorScheme` + **`dynamic_color`**; Apple — `CupertinoColors` / semantics; keep **meaning** (primary/error/success) without cloning one v0 palette everywhere.
- **Type:** Android — M3 scale, optional display via **named `TextTheme` roles**; Apple — **SF** UI; **New York** / **SF Pro Rounded** short roles only; **Dynamic Type** via theme-relative styles.
- **Layout:** Phone — bottom/tab; tablet — split/rail/two-pane; desktop — shortcuts/menus/mouse; tooltip copy **trackpad vs touchpad** via l10n/branches.
- **Motion:** Respect **`MediaQuery.disableAnimationsOf`** + reduce-motion. Android — Material motion, **predictive back**. iOS — **Cupertino** routes where Cupertino stack. **Haptics** primary actions — per-platform tuning.

## Repo layout
| Area | Rule |
|------|------|
| `lib/core/` | Tokens, shells, extensions — **no feature imports** |
| `lib/features/<name>/` | `presentation/`, `application/` (providers), optional `data/` |
| `lib/l10n/` | `.arb` → generated `app_localizations*.dart` |
| OCR | `ReceiptOcrChannel` + `MethodChannel` (`lib/core/ocr/`): Android **ML Kit** `MainActivity`, iOS **Vision** `SceneDelegate`; **parse/heuristics in Dart** (`receipt_line_parse.dart`, `receipt_ocr_refiner.dart`); **`probe`** early; OCR fail **must not** block manual entry (`runReceiptScanFlow`, add-item). **Persisted money** → **Rust**. |
| `rust/src/` | `api/` FRB thin; `domain/` money+invariants; `ledger/` or `settlement/` splits + future CRDT **helpers** (transport in Flutter/plugin). Split up `simple.rs` as features grow. |

## Persistence roadmap
| | MVP | Later |
|---|-----|--------|
| Storage | Encrypted SQLite (SQLCipher-class); ~5–15% overhead OK; encrypt PII/payment fields | + optional plaintext export (opt-in) |
| Backup | Manual **`.sb_backup`** (or agreed ext.), encrypted; user stores Drive/iCloud/email; **import** on-device; **no** custom cloud MVP | Scheduled; optional unencrypted export |
| Sync | **Deferred** — paths allow future layer | Nextcloud/iCloud paths, **CRDT** (**Automerge** / **Yrs**), deterministic merge |

**MVP rule:** Persistence = **Flutter + SQLite + channels**; Rust takes **snapshots/commands** from Dart — **no** raw sockets in MVP.

## OCR (no in-app LLM)
Android **ML Kit** text; iOS **Vision** `VNRecognizeTextRequest`. Flow: shutter → **live editable chips**; lines = heuristic + user fix; Rust **canonical** after confirm. **No** transformer in-app MVP; server assist = later.

## Money
Persist **`CurrencyAmount`**: value + **ISO 4217** + documented scale (Rust). FX later = **non-destructive** (new tables / nullable FX). FRB mirrors shape; **no** naked `f64` without currency in storage.

## Post-MVP sync
**CRDT** offline concurrent edits; **deterministic** merge. Evaluate **Automerge-rs** / **Yrs** + Dart bridge vs WASM — **record decision** in repo; **don’t block MVP**.

## Shell extras
Same **nav graph** everywhere — M3E (Android) vs LG shell (Apple); only chrome/controls differ. **Fluid bottom bar** (morphing center **+**, **soft labels** Trips/Balances, horizontal carousels): when shell ready — don’t abstract before second tab. **Rive**: hero motion if worth it — **few** assets; **120fps** aspirational on ProMotion.

## Localization
New strings → **`app_en.arb` first** with `@key` + `description` (context, DNT terms). Other locales: `app_<code>.arb`; crowdsourcing via **GitHub PRs** to ARBs + optional Weblate/Crowdin/Tolgee; MT → human review. **`l10n_untranslated.txt`** from `flutter gen-l10n`. Runtime: device default + settings override.

## Security
**SQLCipher-class** local DB. Backups **encrypted** by default; UX for passphrase / keychain.

## MVP — “Perfect Local Utility”
**Goal:** Flawless **offline** tool first — **no** Nextcloud/multi-device sync in MVP.

| Pillar | Ships |
|--------|--------|
| Encrypted DB | At-rest encryption (device loss/theft) |
| Snap & Split | **ML Kit** / **Vision** only — no LLM; lines → assign; **Rust** canonical math |
| Manual backup | Encrypted **`.sb_backup`** → user cloud/email; **import** elsewhere |
| Native styles proof | ≥1 screen reads **LG** on iOS, ≥1 **M3 Expressive** on Android — same semantics, dual wrappers |

**Stretch (after DB + backup + scan credible):** IDR-first, trip/group ledger, debt list + **Optimize** (Rust).

**Out of MVP:** Nextcloud/WebDAV, CRDT, FX, in-app LLM, **insights/analytics** (v0-style trends until scheduled), Rive-heavy nav shell (optional).

## Post-MVP backlog
Recurring spend, auto-categories, advanced splits (%/shares/fixed), multi-currency+FX, debt optimizer polish, “who pays next?”, PDF/WhatsApp, **user-chosen sync** (Nextcloud, iCloud paths).

## Cursor / AI
Match existing style; **no** drive-by renames or essay comments; new files follow **repo layout** above unless `tool/` one-off.

